4. Apple (AAPL) weekly stock prices for 2015 (20 points) Please recreate this line graph by using the dataset of Apple (AAPL) weekly stock prices for 2015. The horizontal line is the mean. The data can be found at: http://real-chart.finance.yahoo.com/table.csv?s= AAPL&a=00&b=1&c=2015&d=11&e=31&f=2015&g=w&ignore=.csv using a pipe including the following steps: i. Convert the variable Date to a Date object using mutate() ii. Order the data frame by the variable Date in a increasing order using arrange() iii. Create a factor variable names Change = factor(c(Increase, Decrease, Initial)[c(2, diff(Close) < 0) + 1]) using mutate() iv. Create a null plot using ggplot v. Add points Date against Close using geom_point() with color = Change, shape = Change, fill = Change vi. Add a line graph Date against Close using geom_point() vii. Specify the shapes by scale_shape_manual(values = c(25, 24, 19)) viii. Specify the colors by scale_color_manual(values = c(green, red, gray)) ix. Specify the colors by scale_fill_manual(values = c(green, red, gray))

aapl<-read.csv("http://real-chart.finance.yahoo.com/table.csv?s=AAPL&a=00&b=1&c=2015&d=11&e=31&f=2015&g=w&ignore=.csv",header = TRUE)
aapl %>% mutate( Date=as.Date(Date)) %>% arrange(Date)%>%mutate(Change =factor(c('Increase', 'Decrease', 'Initial')[c(2,
diff(Close) < 0) + 1])) %>% ggplot() + geom_point(mapping = aes(x = Date, y = Close, color = Change,shape = Change, fill
= Change))+ geom_path(mapping = aes(x = Date, y = Close))+scale_shape_manual(values = c(25, 24, 19))+scale_color_manual(values = c('green', 'red', 'gray'))+ scale_fill_manual(values = c('green', 'red', 'gray'))

#5. Permutation test (Bonus 10 points) We have learned the two sample t-test to test the null hypothesis H0: the mean of the Sepal.Width between versicolor and virginica (assuming the variance are the same for the two species). We can extract the observed t-statistics and the p-value by

iris2 <- filter(iris, Species %in% c('versicolor', 'virginica'))
t_obs <- t.test(iris2$Sepal.Width ~ iris2$Species, var.equal = TRUE)$statistic
pv_obs <- t.test(iris2$Sepal.Width ~ iris2$Species, var.equal = TRUE)$p.value
t_obs
##         t 
## -3.205761
pv_obs
## [1] 0.0018191
set.seed(2017)
t_perm<-vector(length=10000)
for(i in 1:10000){
a<-t.test(iris2$Sepal.Width ~ sample(iris2$Species), var.equal = TRUE)$statistic
t_perm<-c(t_perm,a)
}
pv_perm<-sum(abs(t_perm) >abs(t_obs))/10000
pv_perm
## [1] 0.0013
